						               													<description>A fan made expansion designed by David Fair and available for download from the Geek.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules:&amp;#10;https://boardgamegeek.com/filepage/21763/aos-chesapeake-ohio-rulespdf#&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board: (full size PDF, needs to be cut for printing, 24x18&amp;quot; single page)&amp;#10;http://www.boardgamegeek.com/fileinfo.php?fileid=21762&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This map is designed for 4-6 players, and incorporates a number of rules variations, including a modification of Ted Alspach's chain delivery mechanic, and a creative new rule that allows players to place factories onto cities. The factories, in thematic fashion, mean that cities will gain more goods, as each time a delivery is made to the city, two more goods are placed onto it. Factories also give bonus income to their owner when a delivery is made to their locale, but they also increase end of round expenses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
